  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restoring access to life-saving primary healthcare and integrated nutrition services for crisis-affected populations in East Aleppo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">E Aleppo is becoming more accessible and as land continues to be cleared of debris and UXOs, it is expected that the number of returnees will increase. All forms of basic services are at high need. Most houses are damaged and neighborhoods lack basic services

The project will restore access to, and quality of, essential basic health and nutrition services to up to 20,000 beneficiaries through the rehabilitation of one Ministry of Health Primary Healthcare clinic in E Aleppo. The intervention will include repair and rehabilitation of the building, re-equipment, capacity building and a community care programme. . Medair will also carry out minor rehabilitation of a second MoH PHC clinic in E. Aleppo and re-equip it for provision of the all essential PHC services, as well as to provide capacity building and a community care programme. With funding from another donor Medair will then continue support of the soft components for both clinics for a period of 12 months to ensure quality service delivery. Whilst the second clinic is expected potentially to serve more than 25,000 beneficiaries, due to the timing of the intervention, full functionality of the clinic is not anticipated until after the SHF funded project is completed. Protection and nutrition activities will be fully integrated in services of the clinic and also delivered through the community care programme, which is structured around house to house visits by trained community health workers and community volunteers as well as engagement with community groups. Building capacity and knowledge in different layers (household, community and facility) will enable more cohesive and robust support to be provided to vulnerable, conflict-affected individuals and help to build their resilience. 

Medair has an MOU with the Ministry of Health and an established relationship since 2015. Medair staff will be based in Aleppo and deliver the project direct.</narrative>
  </description>
